DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Storage Processing Elapsed Time Minute Duration
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The duration of time in minutes between biospecimen collection, through processing procedure, to final storage.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._The act of safekeeping goods in a depository._The act of preparing or putting through a prescribed procedure._The interval between two reference points in time.
